{"article_id":"2vYdo6qm9dU1HLHN","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Attorney General Jeff Sessions appeared before the Senate Intelligence Committee Tuesday","depth":3},{"id":1,"text":"to address several allegations against him .","depth":3},{"id":2,"text":"Both Chairman Richard Burr","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"( R-NC )","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"and Sen. Mark Warner","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"( D-VA )","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"hoped","depth":5},{"id":7,"text":"he would clear up all questions","depth":4},{"id":8,"text":"relating to the Russia investigation .","depth":4},{"id":9,"text":"Sessions ,","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"who requested an open hearing a day before his testimony ,","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"began his opening statement","depth":5},{"id":12,"text":"by insisting","depth":5},{"id":13,"text":"that such interference by Russia into our election can \" never be tolerated . \"","depth":5},{"id":14,"text":"Then , he proceeded to try and exonerate himself from any wrongdoing , particularly in regards to accusations","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"that he met privately with Russian officials during last year ' s presidential campaign .","depth":6},{"id":16,"text":"\" I did not have any private meetings with any Russian officials \" at the Mayflower hotel last April ,","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"Sessions insisted .","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"He continued to emphasize","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"he had \" no recollection \"","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"of talking with the Russian Ambassador Sergey Kislyak at the reception in question .","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"Besides , it was \" entirely beside the point \" into this investigation into Russia ' s interfering in our elections .","depth":6},{"id":22,"text":"The attorney general then got personal ,","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"shocked","depth":7},{"id":24,"text":"that his former colleagues would accuse him of undermining their democracy .","depth":6},{"id":25,"text":"\" I have never met with or had any conversations with Russians","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"concerning interference with any campaign , \"","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"Sessions reiterated .","depth":7},{"id":28,"text":"\" The suggestion","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"that I participated in any collusion with the Russian government","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"to hurt this country ,","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"which I have served with honor for 35 years ,","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"is an appalling and detestable lie . \"","depth":7},{"id":33,"text":"Many outlets have been obsessed with an exchange","depth":7},{"id":34,"text":"Sessions had with Sen. Al Franken","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"( D-MN )","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"during his confirmation hearing in March .","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"Some argue","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"that the then-senator misled the panel","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"by answering","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"he had never had communications with Russian officials .","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"\" Former colleagues , that is false , \"","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"Sessions said .","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"\" Sen . Franken asked me a rambling question after some six hours of testimony","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"that included dramatic , new allegations .","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"I was taken aback by explosive allegations . \"","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"Sessions said","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"he wanted to refute claims of collusion immediately .","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"So , he offered what he thought was \" a fair and correct response . \"","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"Yet ,","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"when Sessions decided to recuse himself from the Russia investigation ,","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"many took that as a sign of guilt .","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"Sessions cleared up that allegation as well .","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"The attorney general recused himself","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"not because of any wrongdoing ,","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"but because of a DOJ regulation","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"that mandated","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"department employees should not participate in campaign investigations on campaigns","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"in which they served as an advisor .","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"That ' s why he stepped aside .","depth":6},{"id":60,"text":"It is \" absurd \" to suggest otherwise ,","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"Sessions said ,","depth":7},{"id":62,"text":"or that a recusal proves","depth":7},{"id":63,"text":"he would be unable to manage leadership of the DOJ .","depth":7},{"id":64,"text":"Sessions then pivoted to the issue over former FBI Director James Comey ' s firing .","depth":6},{"id":65,"text":"Specifically , he shed some light on the conversation","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"he had with Comey","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"regarding the latter ' s meeting with the president .","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"Comey and Sessions met after a routine morning threat briefing .","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"In that meeting , Comey reportedly shared his concern about proper communications protocol with the White House .","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"Sessions said","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"he agreed with Comey","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"that the FBI and the DOJ need to be careful to follow policies ,","depth":12},{"id":73,"text":"taking care to limit communications with the White House .","depth":12},{"id":74,"text":"Sessions said","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"he was \" confident \"","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"the FBI director would comply .","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"He did not , however , recuse himself from defending himself against false allegations .","depth":6},{"id":78,"text":"\" I have dedicated myself to the highest standards , \"","depth":7},{"id":79,"text":"Sessions concluded .","depth":7},{"id":80,"text":"When it came time for questions ,","depth":7},{"id":81,"text":"several lawmakers wanted Sessions to expand on his involvement in the firing of Comey .","depth":7},{"id":82,"text":"President Trump asked him and Deputy Attorney General Rod Rosenstein for their opinions on Comey and to put it in writing ,","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"Sessions explained .","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"\" There was a clear view of mine and Rosenstein","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"that we had problems \" at the FBI","depth":9},{"id":86,"text":"and it was his best judgment that a \" fresh start \" was the appropriate thing","depth":9},{"id":87,"text":"to do .","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"Comey had proved himself unfit for the job ,","depth":7},{"id":89,"text":"Sessions said ,","depth":7},{"id":90,"text":"because","depth":7},{"id":91,"text":"when he denied prosecution of Hillary Clinton after the email probe ,","depth":8},{"id":92,"text":"that was a \" usurpation of authority . \"","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":185,"left":101,"right":184,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":101,"left":94,"right":100,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":94,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":100,"left":98,"right":99,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":98,"left":95,"right":97,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":95,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":97,"left":96,"right":6,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":96,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":99,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":184,"left":124,"right":183,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":124,"left":105,"right":123,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":105,"left":103,"right":104,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":103,"left":102,"right":11,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":102,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":104,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"attribution","nucleari